My inaugural post is on a delightful word: Enthymeme.
Today someone said to me, &ldquo;He was raised in a Morman cult. Need I say more?&rdquo; The person with whom I was speaking had not outlined what they were thinking, and I had no idea in what sense she meant her question. The answer in the particular situation was an obvious &ldquo;yes.&rdquo;
The expectation on their part (I expect) was that I would say &ldquo;oh yes, of course.
